<div id="review_1367430826" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1367430826" />
    <a title="Charlotte" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/11475773-charlotte"><img alt="Charlotte" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1613443590p2/11475773.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1367430826?book_show_action=true">Aug 18, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Charlotte" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Charlotte" href="/user/show/11475773-charlotte">Charlotte</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/11475773-charlotte?shelf=strange-cities">strange-cities</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/11475773-charlotte?shelf=women-and-nb-of-speculative-fiction">women-and-nb-of-speculative-fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1367430826" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11630684526069789396">If Patricia McKillip burned down my house while chanting &quot;Fenris is the worst Dragon Age character,&quot; I would still log on to Goodreads dot com and give this book five stars. I loved it that much. Like all of her books it&apos;s a cipher and a dreamscape, filled with beautiful imagery, a fascinating, intricate setting and magic that is truly mystical and transformative. I think she has a special knack for writing these wonderful &quot;odd&quot; young female characters like Luna, Peri, Saro and Sybel, and Mag jo</span>
  <span id="freeText11630684526069789396" style="display:none">If Patricia McKillip burned down my house while chanting "Fenris is the worst Dragon Age character," I would still log on to Goodreads dot com and give this book five stars. I loved it that much. Like all of her books it's a cipher and a dreamscape, filled with beautiful imagery, a fascinating, intricate setting and magic that is truly mystical and transformative. I think she has a special knack for writing these wonderful "odd" young female characters like Luna, Peri, Saro and Sybel, and Mag joins their ranks with her own unique struggle and transformation. <br />My main concern ar this point is that I'm all-too quickly running out of McKillip books. I'm not sure if I should space them out to make them last or enjoy them all at once.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11630684526069789396" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


