<span id="freeTextContainer3831363184055976573">We all know the saying &quot;Never judge a book by its cover&quot;, but I ignored this saying, and began this book with a sour attitude because of the cover that was not to my liking. But, we all know that the majority of the time, Kira is very wrong, and I ended up falling in love with this story. Once again, McKillip has woven a beautifully complex tale with amazing decorations adorning it. I feel that the summary on the cover doesn&apos;t show how wonderful the story is, so I will atempt one.<br/> <i>Ombria in Shad</i></span>
  <span id="freeText3831363184055976573" style="display:none">We all know the saying "Never judge a book by its cover", but I ignored this saying, and began this book with a sour attitude because of the cover that was not to my liking. But, we all know that the majority of the time, Kira is very wrong, and I ended up falling in love with this story. Once again, McKillip has woven a beautifully complex tale with amazing decorations adorning it. I feel that the summary on the cover doesn't show how wonderful the story is, so I will atempt one.<br /> <i>Ombria in Shadow</i> focuses mainly on three charachters, who we get very attatched to in the duration of the story. Lydea, the princes mistress, becomes devoted to the princes son, Kyel, and makes it her duty to comfort and protect him, even after the evil regent, The Black Pearl, throws her out onto the street where she won't survive, or at least, not without the help of the mysterious Mag.<br /> Mag, the sorceress's waxling, lives in the undercity of Ombria, with its ghosts and magical creatures. She had spent her entire life working for the sorceress as her helper, her creation, until one day, when she swallows a magical heart, she realizes that she had been human all along, not a child crafted from wax. After learning this, she realizes that she can think, and soon finds herself caught in the affairs of Ombria, and before she knows it, becomes part of its history.<br /> Our last charachter is Ducon, the royal bastard. The out of place charcoal weilder draws things from the bad parts of the city, doors and windows that catch his eye- not knowing what they mean. Once the Black Pearl controls the palace of Ombria, he has pressure from other royalty to take her down, but scared for his young cousin, Kyel's life, he stay obedient until finally, he, Lydea, and Mag put all of the pieces of the mystery of Ombria together. </span>
  <a data-text-id="3831363184055976573" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
