<div id="review_2921725295" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2921725295" />
    <a title="Jen" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/20663015-jen"><img alt="Jen" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1515376148p2/20663015.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2921725295?book_show_action=true">Aug 05, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jen" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jen" href="/user/show/20663015-jen">Jen</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2921725295" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1874213657149000289">4🌟 for certain characters &amp; ideas<br/>2🌟 for writing style &amp; execution...so...<br/>3🌟 overall<br/>Oh this book! So frustrating and absolutely annoying at times. I liked the premise of this book and hoped for good things but the writing😣 By turns confusing and vague, I found the writing so opaque that I read several pages and nothing sunk in. I had to go back and reread paragraphs again and again.<br/>Not very much seems to happen but it clearly does because events construe changes and things change between the begi</span>
  <span id="freeText1874213657149000289" style="display:none">4🌟 for certain characters &amp; ideas<br />2🌟 for writing style &amp; execution...so...<br />3🌟 overall<br />Oh this book! So frustrating and absolutely annoying at times. I liked the premise of this book and hoped for good things but the writing😣 By turns confusing and vague, I found the writing so opaque that I read several pages and nothing sunk in. I had to go back and reread paragraphs again and again.<br />Not very much seems to happen but it clearly does because events construe changes and things change between the beginning and end. How I got there is not wholly clear.<br />This was my first book by this author and while I did not get on with the writing style I loved certain characters - Mag, the Sorceress, Ducon and Lydea were engaging and interesting but so underdeveloped.<br />All in all, a bit of a disappointment but I am glad to have read it as I got to meet characters I grew to care about. The descriptions of Mag, Lydea, Camas Erl and Ducon (their eyes, their hair) were particularly nicely written.<br />Would make a fantastic Studio Ghibli film.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1874213657149000289" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


