<div id="review_1553003959" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1553003959" />
    <a title="Akkisuitok" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/52826337-akkisuitok"><img alt="Akkisuitok" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1589479515p2/52826337.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1553003959?book_show_action=true">Dec 11, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Akkisuitok" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Akkisuitok" href="/user/show/52826337-akkisuitok">Akkisuitok</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/52826337-akkisuitok?shelf=2019-books">2019-books</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/52826337-akkisuitok?shelf=c-female-protagonist">c-female-protagonist</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/52826337-akkisuitok?shelf=c-ensemble-cast">c-ensemble-cast</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/52826337-akkisuitok?shelf=c-no-romance">c-no-romance</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1553003959" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer203068740004596729">I last read this as a child, many years ago, and it left a deep impression even as I mostly didn&apos;t understand the many layers of the story. Now it makes more sense to me and I have a different appreciation for the masterful prose and the delicate, fairytale elements of the tale. Patricia McKillip is an underrated master storyteller, who writes fantasy novels that are completely different from the mainstream. This book has everything: magic, interesting protagonists, intrigue, murder, mystery, fo</span>
  <span id="freeText203068740004596729" style="display:none">I last read this as a child, many years ago, and it left a deep impression even as I mostly didn't understand the many layers of the story. Now it makes more sense to me and I have a different appreciation for the masterful prose and the delicate, fairytale elements of the tale. Patricia McKillip is an underrated master storyteller, who writes fantasy novels that are completely different from the mainstream. This book has everything: magic, interesting protagonists, intrigue, murder, mystery, found families and friendship. It also, in spite of my expectations (I'd mostly forgotten the plot) does not feature any kind of romance (except in background flashbacks of the past), which I found extremely refreshing and unusual.</span>
  <a data-text-id="203068740004596729" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


